cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a new method for deep reinforcement learning that involves attention mechanisms and segmentation of sensory input. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are the most general and encompass a wide range of topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of attention mechanisms and segmentation of sensory input also suggests a focus on computer vision and robotics, which are also likely categories. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests a focus on systems and control, which is the least likely category but still a possibility.
